President Trump expressed his outrage at the recently released Inspector General (IG) report, calling it a disgrace and an attempted overthrow of his government. He also mentioned the upcoming Durham report and expressed his belief that the findings will be even more damning. The President then shifted the conversation to the topic of education and the importance of expanding school choice. Several individuals, including Vice President Mike Pence, Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos, and various lawmakers, shared their support for school choice and discussed the positive impact it can have on students. They also mentioned the need for educational reform and the importance of empowering parents to make choices about their children's education. The President concluded the meeting by thanking everyone for their contributions and expressing his commitment to fighting for education freedom.